com.ibm.ecm.api.coresdk.model

Class IBMECMCompletionHandler<T>

  • Object
    • IBMECMCompletionHandler<T>

  • public abstract class IBMECMCompletionHandler<T>
extends Object
    This class processes results of asynchronous calls. Each asynchronous call requires that you provide an appropriately parameterized instance of this class.

    The completion of the asynchronous call is always performed on a background thread. It is not performed on the same thread as the original caller. This means for mobile applications, such as Android, the completion handler needs to be posted to the main thread if the callback is used to update an Android user interface.
